The paper discusses post-quantum cryptography, which is a subfield of cryptography that deals with cryptographic protocols that are resistant to quantum attacks. This falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses non-commutative algebraic structures and their application to various asymmetric protocols, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents a framework for GL(d,F_p) matrices, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses zero-knowledge proof authentication, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the security of the proposed framework, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
